Reasoning: The paper focuses on word sense disambiguation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses supervised and unsupervised learning methods, which are common topics in machine learning (ML). Therefore, the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely. Finally, the paper mentions the use of Gibbs Sampling and the Expectation Maximization (EM) algorithm, which are common in statistical modeling and inference. Therefore, the sub-category cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing, Statistical Learning) is also a possibility.
